    "title": "BV2182 — Why STAR Has an Automatic Runoff — a Runoff Reversal, with an Equal-Support ballot",
    "description": "STAR FAQ teaching example: why STAR has a second round. 10 voters, three candidates. Berry is the consensus choice and leads the Scoring Round on total stars (44), but more voters strictly prefer Almond head-to-head, so Almond wins the Automatic Runoff 6-3 — a clean 'score leader != runoff winner' Runoff Reversal. One voter scored both finalists 5 (Equal Support) and is counted in neither runoff column. Almond is also the Condorcet winner here.",
